Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Positioned at the top of the city’s most influential street, QV1 is regarded as Perth’s most sought after corporate address. 

A 38 storey premium office tower designed by internationally renowned architect Harry Seidler, there is no other office tower in the Perth CBD that has been more thoughtfully designed or more elegantly finished. 

To this day QV1 remains one of Australia’s most iconic and beautiful office buildings. 

Contiguous full floors are now available within this iconic modernist building.

Life at the top comes with its privileges. Everything you expect of an office tower of this standard and quality is waiting for you right now.

THE BUILDING:
Premium grade office accommodation 
Fully refurbished or fitted full floors
1,600 - 1,700 sqm floor plates
Column free floor space
Floor to ceiling double glazed glass windows
Vertical and horizontal shades to reduce heat and sunlight glare
Excellent views of Swan River, Kings Park and across the city
Access flooring throughout

THE PREMISES
Level 37 & 38: 2,514 sqm - Top of the building tenancy with double height void reception area & inter-floor stairs. To be provided fully refurbished. Excellent views of the ocean, river and across the city.  
Level 33: 362 sqm - to be fully refurbished with excellent river views.
Level 33: 402 sqm - brand new spec fitout with 28 workstations, boardroom, 2 meeting rooms, 2 quiet rooms and kitchen / breakout. River, ocean and Kings Park views. 
Level 8: 1,654 sqm - fully refurbished floor.
Level 7: 1,654 sqm - currently fully fitted, can be provided refurbished open plan. 
Level 6: 1,653 sqm - currently fully fitted, can be provided refurbished open plan. 
Level 5: 1,631 sqm - currently fully fitted, can be provided refurbished open plan. 
Level 4: 1,608 sqm - fully refurbished floor. 

Further floors may be available.
 
AMENITIES:
New premium quality 'end of trip' facilities
New landscaped retail plaza 
Conference center with 80 seat theatrette plus meeting rooms
Concierge service
Fitness centre
New childcare centre
3 tennis courts and basket ball court
874 bay public car park
155 executive car park
Community garden, plus bees and chickens
New wellness room with weekly yoga and pilates classes.

SUSTAINABILITY:
5.5 Star NABERS Energy rating
6 Star NABERS Indoor Environment rating
4 Star NABERS Water rating

Energy efficient lighting
Advanced building monitoring.

A full lift upgrade, including DCS and car refurbishment commenced Q4 2019.

Ground floor lobby planning commenced Q4 2019. Works expected to commence Q2 2021.
